WEBVTT

00:05.518 --> 00:08.118
<i>The Times</i> wants an interview
regarding

00:08.119 --> 00:09.720
the new Critical
Response Command.

00:09.722 --> 00:12.556
Refer them to the Chief
of Counterterrorism. Thank you.

00:12.558 --> 00:13.724
They want you.

00:13.726 --> 00:15.292
They're lucky if
anyone in this department

00:15.294 --> 00:17.394
talks to 'em after
that hack job they did

00:17.396 --> 00:19.563
on excessive force in the NYPD.

00:19.565 --> 00:21.165
That was a different reporter.

00:21.167 --> 00:23.300
And I wasn't aware
that you read <i>The Times.</i>

00:23.302 --> 00:24.568
I do. For laughs.

00:24.570 --> 00:25.836
What's next?
City Council

00:25.838 --> 00:28.439
Speaker Thomas
was sworn in yesterday.

00:28.441 --> 00:30.174
Oh, another cop-hater.

00:30.176 --> 00:32.543
Here's an idea:
let's limit these briefings

00:32.545 --> 00:34.611
to “things that Frank
doesn't know.”

00:34.613 --> 00:37.548
Her press conference after
was about how her top priority

00:37.550 --> 00:39.883
is dismantling
our Broken Windows policy.

00:39.885 --> 00:42.486
She's been a broken record
about that for years.

00:42.488 --> 00:45.355
As a councilwoman.
Now she's the Speaker.

00:45.357 --> 00:46.724
Now she has muscle.

00:46.726 --> 00:49.593
We base our decisions
on the Broken Windows paradigm.

00:49.595 --> 00:51.729
The moment someone tells me
I can't

00:51.731 --> 00:53.897
is the moment I'm out of here.
Period.

00:53.899 --> 00:55.699
There's no doubt
that poor

00:55.701 --> 00:57.901
and minority neighborhoods
are being singled out

00:57.903 --> 01:00.571
in the enforcement
of minor offenses.

01:00.573 --> 01:02.973
Only because that's where
most of the offenses occur.

01:02.975 --> 01:04.641
But you can't say that.
I just did.

01:04.643 --> 01:05.642
I mean he can't.

01:05.644 --> 01:06.877
I will,

01:06.879 --> 01:08.846
if she pushes me.
Look, it's her own constituents

01:08.848 --> 01:11.582
that'll be hurt the most
if we look the other way.

01:11.584 --> 01:12.750
Well, she is.

01:12.752 --> 01:15.652
Pushing. Legislation
that will decriminalize

01:15.654 --> 01:17.488
several lower-level offenses.

01:17.490 --> 01:18.989
She's proposed
that bill before

01:18.991 --> 01:20.691
and lost, handily.

01:20.693 --> 01:21.658
To review:

01:21.660 --> 01:23.527
Now she's the Speaker.

01:23.529 --> 01:25.462
Now she has muscle.

01:25.464 --> 01:27.431
So do I.

01:27.433 --> 01:28.799
You don't want
to go to war

01:28.801 --> 01:30.801
with the new Speaker
her first week in office.

01:30.803 --> 01:34.204
Let me set up a meeting,
find common ground.

01:34.206 --> 01:36.373
If there were common ground
between the speaker and me,

01:36.375 --> 01:38.308
we would have found it
a long time ago.

01:38.310 --> 01:40.377
“Talk first. Fight last.”

01:40.379 --> 01:42.112
Frank Reagan.

01:42.114 --> 01:43.480
You do say that, boss.

01:45.518 --> 01:46.717
Fine.

01:47.553 --> 01:49.319
Set up a meeting
with the Speaker.

01:49.321 --> 01:50.587
And you'll play nice?

01:50.589 --> 01:54.792
Right up until nice
doesn't work.

01:57.663 --> 01:59.496
Thank you for coming,
Attorney General Schneiderman.

01:59.498 --> 02:01.565
I'm so sorry
for your loss, Your Honor.

02:02.935 --> 02:05.135
Good to see you, Erin.
Nice to see you, sir.

02:06.572 --> 02:07.571
Oh, Zach.

02:07.573 --> 02:09.406
I can't believe she's gone.

02:09.407 --> 02:11.675
That makes two of us.

02:11.677 --> 02:13.110
How are the kids holding up?

02:13.112 --> 02:15.145
Ellen was a wonderful mother.

02:15.147 --> 02:16.446
They depended
on her.

02:16.448 --> 02:17.815
We all did.
I hear

02:17.817 --> 02:20.450
they charged the driver
that caused the accident.

02:20.452 --> 02:24.087
His blood alcohol level
was twice the legal limit.

02:24.089 --> 02:26.156
His third DWI.

02:26.158 --> 02:28.225
You know, when I first started

02:28.227 --> 02:30.694
working at the
DA's Office for you,

02:30.696 --> 02:32.029
Ellen used to
bring me sandwiches.

02:32.031 --> 02:34.097
She used to tell me
that I was too skinny.

02:35.434 --> 02:36.867
Me, too.

02:36.869 --> 02:39.770
Then when I became a judge,
she started bringing salads.

02:39.772 --> 02:41.905
Told me I was getting fat
sitting around all day.

02:44.376 --> 02:46.043
Do you need anything?

02:46.045 --> 02:48.312
I'm okay, Erin.

02:48.314 --> 02:50.814
I hear that you didn't postpone
the sentencing hearing

02:50.816 --> 02:51.949
for this afternoon.

02:51.951 --> 02:53.984
I thought you might
take some time off.

02:54.854 --> 02:57.221
I need to work.

02:57.223 --> 03:01.124
Once the kids go home
and the dust clears...

03:01.126 --> 03:03.126
it's just gonna be me.

03:03.128 --> 03:05.863
A lot of people love you,
including me.

03:05.865 --> 03:07.598
You're not alone.

