03:17.376 --> 03:19.309
Linda.
Hey.

03:19.311 --> 03:20.141
Thanks for coming, Danny.

03:20.165 --> 03:22.437
Look, I know you're pissed
I told Sean

03:22.648 --> 03:24.140
he could keep playing hockey,
but can't we just...

03:24.164 --> 03:24.848
I am.

03:24.850 --> 03:26.116
But that's not why
I asked you to come here.

03:26.118 --> 03:27.150
Hi, Maria.

03:27.152 --> 03:29.052
Hey. What's going on?

03:29.054 --> 03:31.822
Uh, one of the accountants here

03:31.824 --> 03:33.757
is having trouble
with her ex-husband.

03:33.759 --> 03:35.225
Linda, we can't
just get involved...

03:35.227 --> 03:38.195
Her name is Lori D'Angelo,
and she's a friend of mine.

03:38.197 --> 03:41.298
Can we talk to her?
Mm-hmm.

03:41.300 --> 03:44.635
Lori, we're Detectives
Reagan and Baez.

03:45.938 --> 03:48.705
I'm sorry to bother you guys.

03:50.109 --> 03:51.942
Why don't you tell us
what's going on.

03:51.944 --> 03:54.077
Well, I've been divorced
for a year.

03:54.079 --> 03:56.713
My ex can't let go.

03:56.715 --> 03:57.614
What's his name?

03:57.616 --> 03:59.116
Ronald D'Angelo.

03:59.118 --> 04:00.751
He's not a bad guy.

04:00.753 --> 04:04.288
He just keeps stopping by
and watching the building.

04:04.290 --> 04:06.256
It-It's not fair to us.

04:06.258 --> 04:07.791
Who's “us”?
Our son,

04:07.793 --> 04:09.793
Matthew. He's nine.

04:09.795 --> 04:11.795
Ronnie has visitation rights.

04:11.797 --> 04:13.897
I've put up with his
behavior in the past

04:13.899 --> 04:15.632
for Matthew's sake, but...

04:15.634 --> 04:17.834
then I started dating Paul.

04:17.836 --> 04:18.869
And Ronnie didn't like that.

04:18.870 --> 04:20.370
He freaked out.

04:20.372 --> 04:23.674
He, um, started taking Matthew
without asking

04:23.676 --> 04:25.042
and making threats.

04:25.044 --> 04:26.343
I just...

04:26.345 --> 04:29.446
Did you file a complaint?

04:30.616 --> 04:32.416
Well, I-I didn't want to get
the police involved,

04:32.418 --> 04:33.750
but...

04:33.752 --> 04:36.620
well, after last night...

04:36.622 --> 04:38.889
Ronnie and Paul
got into a big argument.

04:38.891 --> 04:40.223
It was awful.

04:40.225 --> 04:42.259
And Matthew saw all of it.

04:42.261 --> 04:44.728
This is
a very unfortunate situation.

04:44.730 --> 04:45.497
I'm just not sure that we...

04:45.521 --> 04:46.898
Why don't you tell us
where we can find

04:46.899 --> 04:49.199
your husband. We'll talk to him.

04:52.271 --> 04:54.237
Thank you, Detectives.

04:56.041 --> 04:58.375
Mr. Greer, you've been
convicted of assault.

04:58.377 --> 05:01.211
The court will now consider
your sentence.

05:01.213 --> 05:02.846
Counsel?

05:02.848 --> 05:05.549
My client deeply regrets
his actions, Your Honor.

05:05.551 --> 05:07.617
He has no criminal record,
and his wife

05:07.619 --> 05:10.654
has taken responsibility
for her role in the incident.

05:10.656 --> 05:14.491
We request the court show
leniency in this matter.

05:14.493 --> 05:15.792
Ms. Reagan?

05:15.794 --> 05:17.894
The People have
no objection.

05:18.764 --> 05:21.231
Mr. Greer, if I go easy on you,

05:21.233 --> 05:23.233
will you promise
not to do it again?

05:23.235 --> 05:24.868
Yes, Your Honor.

05:25.704 --> 05:27.504
When you married your wife,

05:27.506 --> 05:29.873
did you promise to honor
and cherish her?

05:31.110 --> 05:33.010
Don't look
at your lawyer.

05:33.012 --> 05:34.611
Did you make that promise?

05:34.613 --> 05:36.213
Yes, sir.

05:36.215 --> 05:37.581
Then you committed violence
against her.

05:37.583 --> 05:39.549
You broke that promise.

05:39.551 --> 05:42.853
So why should I believe
you'll keep your promise to me?

05:42.855 --> 05:44.454
Your Honor...
I hereby

05:44.456 --> 05:46.189
sentence you
to the maximum sentence

05:46.191 --> 05:48.525
of seven years in state prison.

05:48.527 --> 05:49.893
We're adjourned.

